<script type="text/javascript">
    $(".button").attr("data-dropdown-id", "dropdownMenuBtn").on("click", function(event) {
        var dropdownMenu = $("#dropdownMenu");
        var nestedDropdownMenus = $(".sub-nav__nested-dropdown");
        
        if ($(this).attr("aria-expanded") === "false") {
            $(this).attr("aria-expanded", "true");
        } else {
            $(this).attr("aria-expanded", "false");
        }

        toggleDropdown(dropdownMenu);;
        
        // close all nested dropdown menus if open
        nestedDropdownMenus.each(function() {
            if ($(this).hasClass("show")) {
                $(this).removeClass("show");
                $(this).addClass("hidden");
            }
        })
    })
    $(".sub-nav__nested-button").on("click", function(event) {
        var currentButtonId = $(this).attr("id")
        var nestedDropdownMenu = $(`#nestedDropdownMenu--${currentButtonId}`)
        $(this).find(".chevron").toggleClass("active");

        if ($(this).attr("aria-expanded") === "false") {
            $(this).attr("aria-expanded", "true");
        } else {
            $(this).attr("aria-expanded", "false");
        }

        toggleDropdown(nestedDropdownMenu);
    })
    function toggleDropdown(menu) {
        if (menu.hasClass("hidden")) {
            menu.removeClass("hidden");
            menu.addClass("show");
            
            //add click listener to check for clicks outside of the nav
            //https://stackoverflow.com/questions/152975/how-do-i-detect-a-click-outside-an-element/3028037#3028037
            $(document).click(function(event) { 
                var $target = $(event.target);
                if(!$target.closest('#subNavContainer').length) {
                    closeDropdown(menu);
                }
            });
            
            //add listener for escape key
            $(document).on('keydown', function(event) {
                if (event.key == "Escape") {
                    closeDropdown(menu);
            }});
        } else {
            menu.removeClass("show");
            menu.addClass("hidden");
        }
    }

    function closeDropdown(menu) {
        var dropdownMenu = $("#dropdownMenu");
        var nestedDropdownMenus = $(".sub-nav__nested-dropdown");  
        $(".button").attr("data-dropdown-id", "dropdownMenuBtn").attr("aria-expanded", "false");
        nestedDropdownMenus.each(function() {
            if ($(".button").attr("data-dropdown-id", "dropdownMenuBtn").hasClass("show")) {
                $(".button").attr("data-dropdown-id", "dropdownMenuBtn").removeClass("show");
                $(".button").attr("data-dropdown-id", "dropdownMenuBtn").addClass("hidden");
            }
        })
        menu.removeClass("show");
        menu.addClass("hidden");
    }

</script>

                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="body2 text-start col-12 col-sm-8"><p>Cal Poly Pomona has over 400 scholarship opportunities to support our students&#8217; educational goals. Funding for our scholarships has been provided by generous donors to Cal Poly Pomona who believe in higher education and your ability to achieve academic success.&#160;</p>
<p>The <a href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP)</a> allows students to apply for university scholarships via one application. The Office of Financial Aid &amp; Scholarships coordinates the scholarship application and awarding process with core committees from the various colleges, departments and organizations responsible for selecting recipients.</p>
<p><strong><a class="btn" href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Apply for Scholarships Now!</a></strong></p>
<p><iframe allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/AWgC6Ve7fhY" title="Bronco Scholarship Portal" width="560"></iframe></p></div>

                            <div class="organism-spacer cta-green-card__header spacer__padding-top--small spacer__padding-bottom--small">
                                <section class="standard-text body2 cta-green-card" id="content-section-2">
                        <div class="container">
                            <div class="row">
                               
                                     <header class="cta-green-card__header text-start col-12 col-sm-8">
                                                                        <h2 class="h4__proxima">What is Scholarship Fest?</h2>
                                                                </header>
                            </div>
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="body2 text-start col-12 col-sm-8"><iframe allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" height="314" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-audxpBFjic" title="What is Scholarship Fest?" width="560"></iframe></div>

                <div class="organism-spacer spacer__padding-top--small spacer__padding-bottom--small">
            <section class="faq">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <header class="faq__header col-lg-9">
                            <h2 class="h5__proxima">Cal Poly Pomona Scholarships FAQs</h2><br/>
                            <p class="body2"></p>
                        </header>
                        <div class="accordion__items col-lg-9">
                            
                                                                                    
                                                                                    
                            <section class="accordion" role="tablist">
                                <div class="accordion__item">
                                    <button aria-expanded="false" aria-label="What types of scholarships does Cal Poly Pomona offer?" class="accordion__header" tabindex="0">
                                        <h3 class="h6__proxima">What types of scholarships does Cal Poly Pomona offer?</h3>
                                        <div class="accordion__item--right">
                                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion-chevron" fill="none" height="17" viewBox="0 0 29 17" width="29">
                                                <path d="M27 1.5L14.5 14.5L2 1.5" stroke="#005030" stroke-width="3"/>
                                            </svg>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                    <div class="accordion__content" tabindex="0">
                                        <p class="body2"><p>Cal Poly Pomona offers scholarships from various colleges, departments, clubs and organizations. Most of the scholarships offered are awarded during the following academic year.</p>
<p>Students must be admitted to Cal Poly Pomona to begin applying to available scholarship opportunities offered through the Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP).&#160;</p>
<p>Scholarship offers may be extended to students based on one or more of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Educational and career objectives</li>
<li>Scholastic achievements</li>
<li>Demonstrated financial need&#160;as determined by the Free Application for Federal Student Aid (FAFSA) or the California Dream Act Application (CADAA)</li>
<li>Involvement in school or community service</li>
<li>Active affiliation with clubs and organizations</li>
<li>Special qualifications (talent, obstacles overcome, relationships)</li>
</ul>
<p>Eligibility criteria will be verified prior to scholarship disbursement.</p></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </section>
                                                        
                                                                                    
                            <section class="accordion" role="tablist">
                                <div class="accordion__item">
                                    <button aria-expanded="false" aria-label="What is Scholarship Fest?" class="accordion__header" tabindex="0">
                                        <h3 class="h6__proxima">What is Scholarship Fest?</h3>
                                        <div class="accordion__item--right">
                                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion-chevron" fill="none" height="17" viewBox="0 0 29 17" width="29">
                                                <path d="M27 1.5L14.5 14.5L2 1.5" stroke="#005030" stroke-width="3"/>
                                            </svg>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                    <div class="accordion__content" tabindex="0">
                                        <p class="body2"><p><strong>Scholarship Fest is the Official Cal Poly Pomona Scholarship application cycle!&#160; The cycle runs every October 1st through March 2nd for scholarships for the next academic year.</strong></p>
<p><strong><img alt="fest graphic" class="img img-original-size" height="139" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="396"/></strong></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p>The CPP Scholarships are offered by various colleges, departments, clubs, organizations and community members throughout the University. To apply, visit the <a href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/">Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP)</a> and complete the general application.</p>
<p>The application process for students is simple and fast. Based on university and application data, students are automatically matched to scholarships for which they are eligible. Selection of recipients is made by scholarship committees typically composed of university faculty and/or staff from the academic program or campus organization most closely affiliated with the scholarship.</p>
<p><a class="btn" href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/">Apply for Scholarships Now</a></p></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </section>
                                                        
                                                                                    
                            <section class="accordion" role="tablist">
                                <div class="accordion__item">
                                    <button aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Cal Poly Pomona Scholarship Fest Cycle" class="accordion__header" tabindex="0">
                                        <h3 class="h6__proxima">Cal Poly Pomona Scholarship Fest Cycle</h3>
                                        <div class="accordion__item--right">
                                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion-chevron" fill="none" height="17" viewBox="0 0 29 17" width="29">
                                                <path d="M27 1.5L14.5 14.5L2 1.5" stroke="#005030" stroke-width="3"/>
                                            </svg>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                    <div class="accordion__content" tabindex="0">
                                        <p class="body2"><p><strong>Cal Poly Pomona (Scholarship Fest) Cycle<br/> </strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><img alt="Application - Selection - Disbursement" class="img img-original-size" height="433" src="data:image/png;base64," width="250"/></span></strong></p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Application (October 1 - March 2)<br/></span></strong></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<ul>
<li>Visit the <a href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP)</a></li>
<li>Enter all requested information</li>
<li>Select scholarship(s), complete all required criteria and submit your application by the deadline</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Selection (March 3 - June 30)<br/></span></strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Scholarship review committees will review eligible scholarship applicants</li>
<li>Selected recipients will be notified of their award via their @cpp.edu&#160;email and donor thank you letters may be requested from recipients</li>
<li>Financial Aid packages will be adjusted to include scholarship(s) awards</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Disbursement (10 days prior to the start of the semester)<br/></span></strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>Scholarships will be awarded beginning in May and will continue through the summer</li>
<li>Disbursement of scholarships will occur nightly, but not earlier than 10 days prior to the first day of classes for each semester</li>
<li>Make sure to monitor your Bronco Direct account regularly for any Holds, Messages and To Do List items that may be required</li>
</ul>
<p><em><strong>Note</strong>:&#160;Disbursement of a scholarship is dependent on the criteria set by the donor. Recipient&#160;of a scholarship should be aware of the requirements of the awarded scholarship for disbursement.</em></p></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </section>
                                                        
                                                                                    
                            <section class="accordion" role="tablist">
                                <div class="accordion__item">
                                    <button aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Using the Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP)" class="accordion__header" tabindex="0">
                                        <h3 class="h6__proxima">Using the Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP)</h3>
                                        <div class="accordion__item--right">
                                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion-chevron" fill="none" height="17" viewBox="0 0 29 17" width="29">
                                                <path d="M27 1.5L14.5 14.5L2 1.5" stroke="#005030" stroke-width="3"/>
                                            </svg>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                    <div class="accordion__content" tabindex="0">
                                        <p class="body2"><ol>
<li>Go to the the <a href="https://csupomona.academicworks.com/" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP)</a> to review the available scholarships. Not all scholarships are posted at the same time, so be sure to check back every week.</li>
<li>Fill out the general Bronco Scholarship Application (opens October 1<sup>st</sup>).&#160;&#160;</li>
<li>Click on specific scholarships to see additional requirements, such as short statements.&#160;&#160;</li>
<li>Complete any additional supplemental requirements by the deadline.</li>
<li>While Scholarship Fest ends March 2nd, the Bronco Scholarship Portal (BSP) remains open all year as it is used for CSU Systemwide Scholarships as well as other scholarship opportunities.</li>
</ol>

                            </section>
                                                        
                                                                                    
                            <section class="accordion" role="tablist">
                                <div class="accordion__item">
                                    <button aria-expanded="false" aria-label="General Application Essay Prompt(2025-2026 Scholarship Cycle opening October 1st)" class="accordion__header" tabindex="0">
                                        <h3 class="h6__proxima">General Application Essay Prompt(2025-2026 Scholarship Cycle opening October 1st)</h3>
                                        <div class="accordion__item--right">
                                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion-chevron" fill="none" height="17" viewBox="0 0 29 17" width="29">
                                                <path d="M27 1.5L14.5 14.5L2 1.5" stroke="#005030" stroke-width="3"/>
                                            </svg>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                    <div class="accordion__content" tabindex="0">
                                        <p class="body2"><p>In 750 words or less please write a personal statement discussing each of the following:</p>
<ol>
<li>Academic goals</li>
<li>Career objectives</li>
<li>Why this scholarship would be helpful to you</li>
<li><strong>(OPTIONAL) </strong>Any relevant information you feel the committee should take into consideration when reviewing your application, including work, community service, or volunteer experience related to your area of study or otherwise, achievements worthy of mentioning, leadership activities, or any challenges you have encountered while pursuing your educational endeavors.</li>
</ol></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </section>
                                                        
                                                                                    
                            <section class="accordion" role="tablist">
                                <div class="accordion__item">
                                    <button aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Scholarship Essay Writing Tips" class="accordion__header" tabindex="0">
                                        <h3 class="h6__proxima">Scholarship Essay Writing Tips</h3>
                                        <div class="accordion__item--right">
                                            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="accordion-chevron" fill="none" height="17" viewBox="0 0 29 17" width="29">
                                                <path d="M27 1.5L14.5 14.5L2 1.5" stroke="#005030" stroke-width="3"/>
                                            </svg>
                                        </div>
                                    </button>
                                    <div class="accordion__content" tabindex="0">
                                        <p class="body2"><p>Many scholarships require submitting an essay as part of the application. Here are some tips:</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Tips On How To Write A Personal Essay</span></strong></h3>
<p>What does a scholarship committee look for in a personal essay? The committee usually looks for an essay that demonstrates effort (i.e., neatness and presentation); an essay that showcases excellent writing ability and an essay that reveals the applicant&#8217;s outstanding achievements and personal qualities. You should view your personal statement the same as an in-person job interview, so before you start writing your essay, consider the suggestions written below.</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Conduct an inventory of your accomplishments, personal strengths, and future goals</span></strong></h3>
<p>This process will help you organize your thoughts and structure your essay in a chronological order. It will also help you describe your strengths in such a way that will &#8220;grab&#8221; the readers&#8217; attention making them want to continue reading.</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Review the essay requirements</span></strong></h3>
<p>By understanding what the committee is looking for in a personal statement, you will be able to tailor your essay to meet the scholarship requirements. In other words, you will be able to write an essay that conveys the message that you are the best applicant.</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Write in the active voice and keep your essay short and precise</span></strong></h3>
<p>Scholarship committee members usually have to read hundreds of essays. If your essay is too lengthy and poorly presented, you will lose the readers&#8217; interest and they will stop reading. It is recommended that you write in the active rather than the passive voice. Using the active voice makes your writing stronger. For example, instead of writing, &#8220;The essay writing competition at Cal Poly Pomona was won by me,&#8221; you would want to write, &#8220;I won the essay writing competition at Cal Poly Pomona.&#8221;</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Avoid controversial topics and issues</span></strong></h3>
<p>Since you do not know the readers&#8217; personal beliefs and values, it is best to avoid controversial topics even though you may feel strongly about some of them. This avoids offending and alienating the readers.</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Check your essay for grammar, typos and punctuation</span></strong></h3>
<p>Before submitting your essay, make sure that it is flawless. This means that your grammar, punctuation, spelling and sentence construction should be perfect. Ask your brother, sister, friend or English professor to proofread your essay for grammatical errors and typos. Write clearly with concise and well-chosen words.</p>
<h3><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Be original</span></strong></h3>
<p>Write your essay with originality, sincerity and from your heart.</p></p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </section>
                                                         
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>
